<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="ease-v">ease <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /iːz/    美 /iːz/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>减轻；缓解：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>ease the pain</strong> / <strong>stress</strong> / <strong>burden</strong>
减轻疼痛/压力/负担</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The situation has eased. 
情况已经缓和了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It would <strong>ease my mind</strong> to know where he was.
要是知道他在哪儿我就放心了。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>小心缓慢地移动：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She eased her injured foot into her shoe. 
她小心翼翼地把受伤的脚伸进鞋里。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="ease-sb-oneself-into">ease (sb / oneself) into</h3>
<p>1.<strong>(使某人) 熟悉 (新工作等)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>After the baby, she eased herself back into work. 
生完孩子她又重新开始工作了。</p></div></div>